eNCA's Ronald Masinda was at the service. #eNCA #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Max Coleman has been described as a selfless individual who stood for non-racialism and equality for all. A memorial service has been held in Cape Town for the former human rights commissioner and anti-apartheid activist. He died on 16 January at the age of 95. Several anti-apartheid activists and leaders have paid tribute to Coleman. eNCA's Ronald Masinda was at the service and has more details in the video above.